=== Pottery and stone art ===
Contrary to expectations, very few stone [[relief|relieves]] and sculptures were found during excavations,<ref name="Marr"><U+041C><U+0430><U+0440><U+0440> <U+041D>. <U+042F>., <U+041E><U+0440><U+0431><U+0435><U+043B><U+0438> <U+0418>. <U+0410>. <U+0410><U+0440><U+0445><U+0435><U+043E><U+043B><U+043E><U+0433><U+0438><U+0447><U+0435><U+0441><U+043A><U+0430><U+044F> <U+044D><U+043A><U+0441><U+043F><U+0435><U+0434><U+0438><U+0446><U+0438><U+044F> 1916 <U+0433><U+043E><U+0434><U+0430> <U+0432> <U+0412><U+0430><U+043D> (Archaeological Expedition in 1916 to Van), Petrograd, 1922</ref> although the relieves of the Assyrian king [[Sargon II]] depicting the Urartian city of [[Musasir]] clearly show large statues.<ref name=c148/> Only a few minor remnants of stone reliefs were discovered in Turkey, and the rest was likely destroyed after the fall of Urartu. However, pottery items were found in large numbers.<ref>Chahin, 160</ref>

